<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="e6c017f9-3d65-56dc-9c2c-ab6d6db6376f" activityNameId="85c65f6c-8ebc-4e5d-af81-d1e922898871" parentActivityId="c334ede0-580d-4689-a500-59e4fe085179" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">cement production, Portland</activityName>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">CEM I 42.5 N</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Portland cement</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">CEM I</synonym>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">From the reception of raw materials at the cement factory.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">This activity ends with the Portland cement produced in the cement silos (after milling). The dataset does not include packaging and administration.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The information details the manufacturing of Portland cement using milled limestone and gypsum as fillers. Tunisia has five types of cement (CEM I) based on the supplementary cementitious materials (limestone). In terms of mass composition, CEM I has 5% to 10% limestone filler. Tunisian standards (NT 47.01 (2017)) specify the five cement types. Tunisian cement output is represented by five different kinds of cement. The table below summarizes the various cement kinds and compositions as defined by Tunisian specifications (NT 47.01).(2017). Clinker, gypsum, and limestone made CEM I cement (see composition in the table). This dataset covers data from the clinker stockpile to the cement suitable for bulk shipment. After cooling from the rotary kiln, the clinker is pulverized in ball mills to particles less than 75 mm in size. It is then transported to silos and combined with calcium sulfate (gypsum) and limestone. The combined cement is transported to a finishing mill and then kept in cement silos until it is delivered in bulk or packaged (kraft paper). Primary data was collected from one cement factory in Tunisia, who informed the total values of cement production inputs and outputs in 2019. Primary and secondary raw materials and fuels, auxiliary materials, energy, and water use were all recorded. It equates to a 15% market share. Particulate emissions may occur. However they are not recorded owing to a lack of data for the cement grinding phase (air emissions are monitored for the integrated clinker-cement plant as a whole and reported in the clinker production process).</text>
          <imageUrl index="1">https://db3.ecoinvent.org/images/910a96c9-7e41-4964-9381-bbf6f05378f1</imageUrl>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">NT47.01(2017): Ciment - Partie 1: Composition, spécifications et critères des conformité des ciments courants</text>
          <imageUrl index="3">https://db3.ecoinvent.org/images/5a8a9627-ca21-451d-9001-95d338647294</imageUrl>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="36cd730c-4485-4fe9-8efe-8850f771796d">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">2394:Manufacture of cement, lime and plaster</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="133fc02a-7d7e-11de-9ae2-0019e336be3a">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">TN</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The dataset represents the Portland cement production for Tunisia.</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">In Tunisia, all cement production is through dry kiln process. The clinker (90-95%) is ground with gypsum (3-5%) and depending on the type of cement and technical standard (NT-47.01 2017 Eqv EN 197-1) with other materials such as limestone (5 to 10%) to produce the Portland cement.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">The production values for Portland cement, which include the amounts of clinker, limestone, silica sand, and gypsum, are derived from the historical annual production statistics of a specific cement plant in 2019. Although these values are lower than the standard in Tunisia, similar values were observed in other cement plant. It is important to highlight that silica sand and limestone serves as a substitute for clinker in the production of this particular Portland cement.</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2019-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Time period corresponds to data collection period (2019).</text>
        </comment>
      </timePeriod>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
